  "market_context": "London/New York session overlap; daily chart shows breakout above key resistance, 1H shows smooth uptrend with multiple FVGs, 5M confirms reversal via CHoCH after pullback.",
  "key_observation": "After daily breakout and 1H uptrend with FVGs, price formed a CHoCH on 5M, then generated multiple order blocks during the upward move—each offering valid long entries.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst confirmed the daily timeframe showed a breakout above a key resistance level, indicating buyers are in control and aligning with higher-timeframe bullish bias.",
    "Step 2: On the 1-hour chart, analyst identified a smooth uptrend with multiple Fair Value Gaps (FVGs), marking the candle before each imbalance as the optimal trading area for long entries.",
    "Step 3: Analyst zoomed into the 5-minute chart and observed a Change of Character (CHoCH) — a reversal signal confirming the short-term downtrend was over.",
    "Step 4: After CHoCH confirmation, analyst waited for price to form order blocks on the 5M chart and opened long positions at each valid order block with reasonable risk-to-reward, executing multiple trades sequentially without canceling prior ones."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "In strong trends, multiple order blocks can form along the impulse move; traders should enter each with reduced size and proper stop placement to improve risk-to-reward while compounding gains.",
